Pre-Game Insights: South Africa is still in high spirits after finishing third at the recent CAF African Cup of Nations tournament in Ivory Coast.
Algeria comes into the game on the back of a 3-2 victory over Bolivia, with goals from Amine Gouiri, Yassine Benzia, and Mandi.
Bafana Bafana coach Hugo Broos will bring back players like Themba Zwane, Ronwen Williams, and Siyanda Xulu for the match.
Algeria will be without Ismael Bennacer due to injury, while Ramy Bensebaini is doubtful, and Riyad Mahrez was left out of the squad.
